		<div id="comment_body_64989493">Aside from people who are against Musk's intentions because they have an irrational hate for Musk, the biggest hurdle we'll have to get past is people who have a sentimental attachment to the time on the clock, people who are so fixated on the number on the clock that they're less connected with the time of day outside.
<br> <br>The second you start to propose locking the clock and not changing it, plenty of folks will start crying about kids walking to school in the dark because they don't understand that the time on the clock is arbitrary, that we could start school at 1PM or 4AM or whatever, the time on the clock is irrelevant - start school as it pertains to the sun in the sky and not the number on the clock. Once we stick to a time scheme we can adjust society accordingly.<br> <br>
